Question: Do you think it is ok for the government to read your emails for counter-terrorism purposes?
Answer:
I think it is not ok for the government to read my emails for counter-terrorism purposes. It is inappropriate since our emails are private and if other people read them, our privacy no longer exists; let alone the huge work of reading every one's every email, it is almost impossible. But I think it is totally fine that government check some sensitive keywords of our emails to counter- terrorism.